{% block content %}
  <main>
    <h1 class="section-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">A quick, plain-language rundown: what data I keep, why, and how you can see or delete it.</p>

    <div class="policy">
      <p class="updated">Last updated: July 6, 2026</p>

      <h3>Data controller</h3>
      <p>The data controller is the creator of Δέσε Κορδόνια.</p>

      <h3>What data I collect</h3>
      <p>
        If you're just browsing the site, I don't ask you for any personal data. The infrastructure
        providers I use (GitHub Pages, Render, Supabase) may log technical details such as your IP
        address, as part of the normal operation/security of their servers — I don't have access to
        those logs and don't use them to identify you. Your "likes" and "saved" articles are stored
        <strong>locally in your browser</strong> (localStorage) — they never reach me tied to you,
        only an anonymous total like count per article.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you create an account (sign in with an email "magic link", no password), I keep: your
        <strong>email</strong>, optionally your <strong>name</strong> and a short <strong>bio</strong> if you
        fill them in, and whether you want to receive the <strong>newsletter</strong>.
      </p>

      <h3>How I use it &amp; legal basis</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>To sign you in via email with no password, and to remember your profile details — necessary to provide the account you asked for.</li>
        <li>To send you the newsletter — only with your consent, when you opt in.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I don't sell, share, or use your data for advertising.</p>

      <h3>How long I keep it</h3>
      <p>
        Your account details stay stored for as long as your account is active. If you delete your
        account, they're removed from the database immediately.
      </p>

      <h3>Where it's stored</h3>
      <p>Everything I use is hosted within the European Union:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your account (email, name, bio, newsletter preference): database on <a href="https://supabase.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent);">Supabase</a> (Frankfurt, Germany).</li>
        <li>The server (API) that manages it: <a href="https://render.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent);">Render</a> (Frankfurt, Germany).</li>
        <li>Sign-in &amp; newsletter emails are sent via <a href="https://resend.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent);">Resend</a> (Ireland).</li>
        <li>The anonymous like counter, in the same Supabase project — no personal data.</li>
        <li>Traffic is measured anonymously via <a href="https://www.goatcounter.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent);">GoatCounter</a>, with no cookies and no personal data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        I only use one strictly necessary session cookie while you're signed in, so I can recognize you.
        It expires after 7 days or when you sign out. No advertising, profiling, or third-party
        tracking cookies.
      </p>

      <h3>Your rights</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>View and edit your details anytime on the "<a href="account-en.html" style="color:var(--accent);">My account</a>" page.</li>
        <li>Delete your account anytime from the same page — this immediately removes your email, name, bio, and newsletter preference from the database.</li>
        <li>Unsubscribe from the newsletter via the link in every email.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>
        For any question about your personal data or this Privacy Policy, you can reach out at
        <a href="mailto:hello@desekordonia.com" style="color:var(--accent);">hello@desekordonia.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
{% endblock %}

